label.value: increased cellular 2,3-butanediol level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 2,3-butanediol measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased cellular 1-stearoylglycerophosphocholine (18:0) level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 1-stearoylglycerophosphocholine (18:0) measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased cellular cis-aconitate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of cis-aconitate measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased cellular 2-myristoylglycerophosphocholine level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 2-myristoylglycerophosphocholine measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: increased cellular 1-eicosenoylglycerophosphocholine (20:1n9) level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of 1-eicosenoylglycerophosphocholine (20:1n9) measured in a cell is higher than normal.

label.value: abolished cell population growth on gluconate carbon source

value.value: A vegetative cell population growth phenotype in which a cell population does not grow in a medium containing gluconate as the carbon source.

definition.value: Use this term for a population of cells that does not grow with gluconate as the carbon source, but does grow using a different carbon source (a cell population that does not grow on any media would be considered inviable). Note that cell growth terms refer to growth under aerobic conditions unless stated otherwise.

label.value: normal G0 to G1 transition

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the transition from G0 phase (quiescence) to G1 is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: decreased cellular gluconate level

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of gluconate measured in a cell is lower than normal.

label.value: decreased RNA level during cellular response to copper ion during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to copper ions is lower than normal during the meiotic cell cycle. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal RNA level during cellular response to copper ion starvation during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to copper ion starvation and during the meiotic cell cycle is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total RNA or a specific RNA, such as the mRNA transcribed from a gene of interest, may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased level of early meiotic gene mRNA during cellular response to copper ion starvation during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA transcribed from early meiotic genes measured in a cell is lower than normal during a cellular response to copper ion starvation during the meiotic cell cycle. Early meiotic genes are normally transcribed during pre-meiotic S phase and recombination.

label.value: abolished transcription during nitrogen starvation

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which transcription does not occur when the cell is subject to nitrogen starvation. All genes, or a specific subset of genes, may be affected.

label.value: sensitive to idarubicin

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to idarubicin. Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of idarubicin that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: normal growth on etoposide

value.value: A phenotype in which vegetative cell population growth is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) in a medium containing etoposide.

label.value: abnormal SUMO-specific protease activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of SUMO-specific protease activity is abnormal.

label.value: decreased SUMO-specific protease activity

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which the observed rate of SUMO-specific protease activity is decreased.

label.value: abolished DNA binding at STREP motif

value.value: A molecular function phenotype in which DNA binding at a STREP motif by a gene product does not occur, when a gene or the bound DNA sequence is mutated. The affected gene product may be encoded by the mutated gene, or by a different gene.

label.value: increased level of pheromone response gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more pheromone response mRNAs measured in a cell is higher than normal (i.e. higher than observed in wild-type cells). Pheromone response genes are normally transcribed in response to a pheromone stimulus.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: increased level of mating gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more mating mRNAs measured in a cell is higher than normal (i.e. higher than observed in wild-type cells). Mating genes are normally transcribed during conjugation with cellular fusion (i.e. mating).

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: sensitive to sodium arsenite

value.value: A phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which cells show increased sensitivity to sodium arsenite (AsNaO2). Cells stop growing (and may die) at a concentration of sodium arsenite that allows wild type cells to grow.

label.value: increased duration of protein oxidation during vegetative growth

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the duration of oxidation of one or more specific proteins, or of specific protein sites is longer than normal.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal RNA level during mitotic S phase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during S phase of the mitotic cell cycle is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type). Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased protein localization to linear element

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to linear elements is increased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased number of Rad51 foci during meiotic prophase I

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the number of sites at which the protein Rad51 accumulates is lower than normal during prophase of the first meiotic nuclear division.

label.value: abolished protein localization to chromatin during meiosis I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is abolished during the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin during meiosis I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein localization to chromatin

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to chromatin is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to linear element

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to linear elements is decreased.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: branched, swollen, elongated, multinucleate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is branched, has more than one nucleus, and has a larger volume and is longer, than normal. In a swollen cell, both length and diameter may be greater than normal, although the cell is only considered elongated if the length:diameter ratio is also greater than normal.

label.value: inviable branched, swollen, elongated, multinucleate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is inviable, branched, has more than one nucleus, and has a larger volume and is longer, than normal. In a swollen cell, both length and diameter may be greater than normal, although the cell is only considered elongated if the length:diameter ratio is also greater than normal.

label.value: viable branched, swollen, elongated, multinucleate vegetative cell

value.value: A cell morphology phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which a cell is viable, branched, has more than one nucleus, and has a larger volume and is longer, than normal. In a swollen cell, both length and diameter may be greater than normal, although the cell is only considered elongated if the length:diameter ratio is also greater than normal.

label.value: normal protein phosphorylation during cellular response to paraquat

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cellular response to paraquat.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: normal protein phosphorylation during cellular response to 4-nitroquinoline N-oxide

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the phosphorylation of one or more specific proteins is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type) during a cellular response to 4-nitroquinoline N-oxide.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased RNA level during cellular response to copper ion starvation during meiotic cell cycle

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the amount of RNA measured in a cell during a cellular response to copper ion starvation is lower than normal during the meiotic cell cycle. Total RNA or a specific RNA may be affected.

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription. We recommend noting which RNA(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: mitotic spindle elongation during anaphase A

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic spindle elongation takes place during anaphase A. Normally, the spindle elongates immediately following assembly during prophase, remains at a static length during metaphase and anaphase A, and elongates further during anaphase B.

label.value: mitotic spindle collapse without elongation during anaphase B

value.value: A cell phenotype in which a short mitotic spindle assembles and elongates during prophase, but does not elongate further during anaphase B and eventually collapses.

label.value: abolished mitotic spindle elongation during prophase

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic spindle elongation does not occur during prophase. Normally, the spindle elongates immediately following assembly during prophase, remains at a static length during metaphase and anaphase A, and elongates further during anaphase B.

label.value: abolished mitotic spindle elongation during anaphase B

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which mitotic spindle elongation does not occur during anaphase B. Normally, the spindle elongates immediately following assembly during prophase, remains at a static length during metaphase and anaphase A, and elongates further during anaphase B.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to centromere during mitotic metaphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the centromere of a chromosome is abnormal during metaphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased rate of actin cortical patch localization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of actin cortical patch localization is decreased.

label.value: undirected actin cortical patch movement

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which actin cortical patches move within the cell cortex in a less directed manner than normal. The rate of movement may be normal.

label.value: normal rate of actin cortical patch localization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of actin cortical patch localization is normal (i.e. indistinguishable from wild type).

label.value: abnormal lateral attachment of mitotic spindle microtubules to kinetochore

value.value: A cellular process phenotype in which the lateral attachment of sister chromatids to mitotic spindle microtubules is abnormal. Normally, sister chromatids become laterally attached to spindle microtubules as part of mitotic metaphase plate congression. Attachment precedes migration along microtubules towards the spindle equator (metaphase plate).

label.value: increased microtubule polymerization

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which microtubule polymerization, i.e. the addition of tubulin dimers, occurs to a greater extent than normal.

label.value: decreased protein localization to cytoplasm, with protein mislocalized to nucleus, during mitotic interphase

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to the cytoplasm is decreased, and some of the protein is present in the nucleus instead, during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: decreased protein localization to interphase microtubule

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the localization of a protein to a cytoplasmic microtubule is decreased during interphase of the mitotic cell cycle.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: abnormal protein localization to nucleus during meiotic prophase I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is abnormal during prophase of the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: Encompasses both presence of proteins not normally found in the nucleus and decreased levels or absence of proteins normally found there, and describes defects in a localization process. We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: altered level of osmotic stress responsive gene mRNA during vegetative growth

value.value: A cell phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the amount of one or more messenger RNAs that are normally expressed during a cellular response to osmotic stress measured in a cell differs from normal (i.e. is higher or lower than observed in wild-type cells during vegetative growth).

definition.value: Consider annotating to a term describing abnormal transcription or abnormal regulation of transcription, but note that changes in RNA levels may result from changes in RNA stability as well as changes in transcription.

label.value: decreased protein localization to nucleus during prophase I

value.value: A cell phenotype in which the localization of a protein to the nucleus is decreased during prophase of the first meiotic nuclear division.

definition.value: We recommend noting which protein(s) were used in the assay when annotating to this term.

label.value: increased rate of actomyosin contractile ring assembly

value.value: A cellular process phenotype observed in the vegetative growth phase of the life cycle in which the rate, or speed, of contractile ring assembly is increased. Contractile ring assembly is the part of cytokinesis in which the actomyosin contractile ring is formed of actin, myosin, and associated proteins.
